  "text": "where α ≥ 0 and κ, λ, D are as defined in (2). If α = 0 then (5) reduces to [CITATION_1] . If α > 0, then the objective function is strictly convex and so the optimal solution is unique. The term α 2 x 2 is also known as the Tikhonov regularization [CITATION_2] which has been used to handle the ill-conditioning of the operator A in image deconvolution. As we will show later in the paper, in the limit when α ↓ 0, the minimizer of the modified model (5) will converge to the minimizer of (2) with the least Euclidean norm.",
